        "client_msg_id": "d441a224-328d-4912-be48-4d0c65c14ff7",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "My company works specifically with companies that market to software\/devops engineers, and the struggle I hear over and over is about the challenge of wrangling people who are qualified to write this content.  People hired as digital marketing managers for these companies usually try to write content themselves and it's tough to have that resonate, so they try to wrangle their company's engineers, which doesn't work, so they turn to freelance engineers, who typically charge their software development hourly rate, making it enormously expensive.  It's rough",
